                <p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/marvel-rivals/">Marvel Rivals</a> introduced an upgrade to its hero proficiency system last week, allowing players to earn new rewards. Many of these rewards--including the brag-worthy Lord icons--require a considerable amount of grinding to achieve, which has led to the rise of "Lord farming" amongst the playerbase.</p><p>Essentially, players aren't moving after they spawn into a match, as they spam their abilities to earn proficiency points safely. This has led to some <em>very </em>one-sided matches, and developer NetEase says it'll address this problem in a future update. There's no date yet for when this update will go live, but players can expect some severe penalties if they're caught farming stats this way.</p>



    
